produced -->\n| num_episodes         = 8<ref name=\"NovyiKanallastivkahPI\"/>\n| list_episodes        = \n| executive_producer   = \n| producer             = [[Yevhen Tunik]]<ref name=\"10764422tunik\"/>\n| cinematography       = \n| camera               = \n| runtime              = 40 minutes<ref name=\"NovyiKanallastivkahPI\">\n{{in lang|uk}} [https://novy.tv/ua/pershi-lastivki/news/2019/11/25/skilki-seriy-v-pershih-lastivkah/amp/ How many episodes in The First Swallows], [[Novyi Kanal]], (25 November 2019)</ref>\n| company              = \n| distributor          = \n| network              = [[Novyi Kanal]]<ref name=\"NovyiKanallastivkahPI\"/>\n| picture_format       = \n| audio_format         =\n| first_aired          = November 19, 2019<ref name=\"NovyiKanallastivkahPI\"/>\n| last_aired           = \n| related              = \n| website              =\n}}\n\n'''''Early Swallows''''' ({{lang-uk|\u041f\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0456 \u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0456\u0432\u043a\u0438}}, ''Pershi lastivky'') is a [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] [[Ukrainian language]] [[teen drama|teen bullying drama]] television series.<ref name=\"51370821ESBBC\"/>\n\nThe series has been a local surprise hit that deals with subjects including bullying, online harassment, sexual identity and suicide, which are rarely dealt with in public in Ukraine.<ref name=\"51370821ESBBC\">[https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51370821 Ukraine's teen bullying drama that shattered taboos and stirred a nation], [[BBC News]] (12 February 2020)</ref> The programme is broadcast by [[Novyi Kanal]]; the first episode aired in November 2019.<ref name=\"5663355UkrainianTV\">[https://www.kyivpost.com/lifestyle/new-hit-ukrainian-tv-show-for-teenagers-addresses-taboo-subjects.html New hit Ukrainian TV show for teenagers addresses taboo subjects], [[KyivPost]] (10 February 2020)</ref> Its televised episodes attract a viewership of six million viewers on live-to-air television and millions more viewers online.<ref name=\"51370821ESBBC\"/>\n\nThe series title is a reference to the belief that [[swallow]]s are the first sign of spring.<ref name=\"5663355UkrainianTV\"/><ref name=\"hromadske20191207232052\">\n{{in lang|uk}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20191207232052/https://hromadske.ua/posts/pidlitkovij-suyicid-buling-ta-nasilstvo-chi-varto-divitis-serial-pershi-lastivki Teen Suicide, Bulling and Violence: Is It Worth Watching The First Swallows? ], [[hromadske.ua]], (6 December 2019)</ref>\n\n==Production==\nThe first season of ''Early Swallows'' was filmed in two-and-a-half months with a small budget and unknown actors.<ref name=\"hromadske20191207232052\"/> The first season is eight episodes long and {{as of|April 2020|alt=as of April 2020}} a second season is believed to be in production.<ref name=\"obozrevatel20052\">{{in lang|ru}} [https://www.obozrevatel.com/kino/pervyie-lastochki-raskryilsya-final-samogo-otkrovennogo-seriala-v-ukraine-video.htm First Swallows: the finale of the most revealing series in Ukraine was revealed. Video], [[Obozrevatel]], (23 November 2019)</ref> During the writing of the series, writers visited Ukrainian schools and interviewed teenagers on condition of anonymity.<ref name=\"10764422tunik\">{{in lang|uk}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20191231235123/https://www.unian.ua/society/10764422-yevgen-tunik-mozhlivo-pershi-lastivki-pokazhut-shcho-lyudyanist-u-shkoli-sered-vchiteliv-ta-uchniv-zaporuka-togo-shchob-diti-ne-kidalisya-z-vikna.html Yevhen Tunik: Perhaps the First Swallows will show that humanity at school among teachers and students is a guarantee that children do not throw themselves out the window],  [[UNIAN]], 22 November 2019</ref> According to series producer [[Yevhen Tunik]], half of the characters in the programme are based on people they knew.<ref name=\"10764422tunik\"/> Tunik started the writing and pre-production of the series in 2016.<ref name=\"10764422tunik\"/> He had hoped the series would debut in 2018.<ref name=\"10764422tunik\"/> All of the scripts were proofread by lawyers and psychologists but according to Tunik, this did not lead to any script changes.<ref name=\"10764422tunik\"/>\n\nThe title of the series, ''Early Swallows'', is a reference to the belief that [[swallow]]s are the first sign of spring.<ref name=\"5663355UkrainianTV\"/><ref name=\"hromadske20191207232052\"/>\n\n== Synopsis ==\nThe series revolves around the lives of Ukrainian teenagers in a secondary school class.<ref name=\"51370821ESBBC\"/> The teenagers struggle with bullying including the [[Blue Whale Challenge]], lack of parental support, suicidal behaviour, [[LGBT in Ukraine|LGBT]] identity crises\u2014a subject that is rarely portrayed on Ukrainian television\u2014alcoholic parents and speech disabilities..<ref name=\"51370821ESBBC\"/> In one of the show's main plot lines, the main characters are stalked on the Internet by an anonymous person who pretends to be their friend.<ref name=\"n1280302FS\">{{in lang|uk}} {{cite web|url=https://24tv.ua/education/ukrayinskiy_serial_pro_buling_stav_populyarnim_u_sviti_detali_n1280302|title=The Ukrainian series \"First Swallows\" has become popular in the world: details|publisher=[[24 kanal]]|accessdate=13 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n*[[Nina Naboka]] -Valentyna Georgiivna\n*[[Alieksandr Rudinskiy]] - Nick Maslo\n*{{ill|Maksym Samchyk|uk|\u0421\u0430\u043c\u0447\u0438\u043a \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0441\u0438\u043c}} - Fedya Makarov\n*[[Olesya Zhurakivska]] - Larysa Dudka\n\n== Impact ==\n''Early Swallows'' has been praised for making subjects that are rarely discussed in public in Ukraine debatable;<ref name=\"51370821ESBBC\"/><ref name=\"5663355UkrainianTV\"/> bullying is a systemic problem in the country.<ref name=\"51370821ESBBC\"/><ref name=\"5663355UkrainianTV\"/> During each episode, the telephone number of the non-governmental mental health helpline La Strada-Ukraine is displayed;<ref name=\"10764422tunik\"/> within the first month of the series being broadcast, the number of calls to the helpline went up by 600%.<ref name=\"51370821ESBBC\"/> The producers of the series approached La Strada-Ukraine to be involved in the project.<ref name=\"10764422tunik\"/>\n\nAccording to [[BBC News Ukrainian]], the series helped at least one teenage girl to stop trying to commit suicide, and has helped many gay men to [[coming out|reveal their sexual identity]] and others to stop taking part in the Blue Whale Challenge.<ref name=\"51370821ESBBC\"/> In February 2020, ''Early Swallows'' was nominated for two [[Promax Awards]].<ref name=\"ESPA467523\">[https://www.promax.org/docs/default-source/pdfs/europe-finalists-2020.pdf Announcing the 2020 Promax Europe Awards Finalists], [[Promax Awards]] (2020)<br>{{in lang|uk}} {{cite web|url=https://novy.tv/ua/pershi-lastivki/news/2020/02/10/pershi-lastivki-zmagatimutsya-za-prestizhnu-yevropeysku-premiyu/amp/|title=The First Swallows will compete for the prestigious European Prize|publisher=[[Novyi Kanal]]|accessdate=10 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|11632488}}\n* [https://novy.tv/ua/pershi-lastivki/ Series page] on the website of [[Novyi Kanal]] {{in lang|uk}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Early Swallows''}}\n\n[[Category:Teen drama television series]]\n[[Category:2019 Ukrainian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian television series]]\n[[Category:LGBT in Ukraine]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Early Swallows\n| show_name_2          = \n| native_name = \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0456 \u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0456\u0432\u043a\u0438 {{in lang|uk}}\n| italic_title         = no\n| image                = \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0456 \u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0456\u0432\u043a\u0438 (\u0437\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430).png\n| genre                = {{Plainlist|\n* [[teen drama]]\n}}\n| creator              = [[Yevhen Tunik]]<ref name=\"10764422tunik\"/>\n| director             =  [[Valentyn 